comment.body: Updated to correct a problem which occurs when `dwarfdump-classic` is used. Some signed constant values were expressed as large hex values (e.g. `-4` was written as `0xfffffffffffffffc`). When parsed using `strtol()`, overflow would occur and `LONG_MAX` would be returned which when truncated to 32 bits yielding `-1` instead of `-4`. This problem accounted for all the significant differences using `llvm-dwarfdump` vs. `dwarfdump-classic` (the latter was being misinterpreted).

issue.title: [Quickstarts] : Update Custom Istio Enricher (Maven) quickstart to use Fabric8 Istio Extension
issue.body:
### Description
<!--
Thank you for trying out Eclipse JKube!

Please fill out the following information to help us in analyzing the issue, but feel free to skip it if you don't have the information at hand or if it does not apply. Please remove every section which does not apply to the issue.
-->
When we created this quickstart we were using Snowdrop Istio Extension for manipulating Istio objects. This extension was recently migrated to Fabric8: https://github.com/fabric8io/kubernetes-client/issues/3493

https://github.com/eclipse/jkube/blob/7e849a7dd04466ea10684e0c493c3e5dcd5db1ea/quickstarts/kit/custom-istio-enricher/pom.xml#L58-L62

This dependency should be available under fabric8 groupId on [maven central](https://search.maven.org/artifact/io.fabric8/istio-client/5.12.2/bundle):

```xml
<dependency>
  <groupId>io.fabric8</groupId>
  <artifactId>istio-client</artifactId>
  <version>5.12.2</version>
</dependency>
```

- [ ] Change dependency Maven coordinates and version
- [ ] Update code to use updated package names (`me.snowdrop.istio.*` -> `io.fabric8.istio.*`)
- [ ] Make sure quickstart is working correctly as per instructions provided in README

pull_request.title: Add support for RSA-OAEP-256 key management algorithm
pull_request.body:
Fixes #289.

See #289 for all the details and specifically [this comment](https://github.com/eclipse/microprofile-jwt-auth/issues/289#issuecomment-1122205115).
In summary, an `mp.jwt.decrypt.key.algorithm` is introduced to prepare a transition to `RSA-OAEP-256` becoming a default algorithm used to decrypt the content encryption key. `RSA-OAEP` remains a default algorithm in 2.1. `RSA-OAEP-256` will become a new default in the next major release. `mp.jwt.decrypt.key.algorithm` might become a list property too.

CC @teddyjtorres @rdebusscher

issue.title: Configure javac to use --release when building on JDK 9+
issue.body:
We use the maven-compiler-plugin's `maven.compiler.release` property
to configure the --release value when building on JDK 9 or
later. Using --release is preferable to using --source/--target as
--release also factors in the class libraries available in the
release.

Unfortunately, setting this property when building on JDK 8 causes a
build error as the maven-compiler-plugin passes the --release option
to javac which does not understand it. So we use a maven profile to
set the property only when JDK is 9 or higher.

comment.body:
> This is a nice workaround for this issue!

Thanks. I have been using this for a while in all my projects using maven.

pull_request.title: /api/-/query response size
pull_request.body:
Fixes #379 

### Testing steps
- Open this PR in Gitpod.
- Let Gitpod initialize. This can take 5 - 10 minutes, because it will download 485 `vscode.bat` extensions and then publish them to the local instance.
- Get `https://8080-<GITPOD_WORKSPACE_ID>.gitpod.io/api/v2/-/query?extensionId=vscode.bat&includeAllVersions=true`. The response should be ~650 KB.
- For comparison, get `https://8080-<GITPOD_WORKSPACE_ID>.gitpod.io/api/-/query?extensionId=vscode.bat&includeAllVersions=true`. The response should be ~30 MB.

issue.title: Add support to open decompiled symbols through the symbols list
issue.body:
Steps:
- Install java decompiler extension
- Search for a class which doesn't have attached source code.
- Select the class name to open the class

Expectation:
Open the decompiled class source.

Actual:
Nothing happens.

IllegalArgumentException is thrown at Symbol information construction due to lack of proper location. I have a fix for it by resolving the location for BinaryType, I will push it as a PR.
